  "body": "It might be convenient if internal `TASK_COMPILE_COMPILE` consumed a solc output formatter task that other tasks can easily override. Immediate reason for wanting this is that I'm writing something that will inadvertently introduce many warnings. I'd like to suppress them without altering the other logic in that method.\r\n\r\nThis has wider application - for example Federico Bond wrote some nice error formatting for solc that ended up in [this merged PR](https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/pull/5511). It's not enabled by default and disabled for anyone using the JSON I/O interface. That work could be emulated in JS and have additional features:\r\n+ sorting of warnings and errors\r\n+ warning aggregation (e.g display abi-encoder v2 warning once +  number of times);\r\n+ `--no-warn` \r\n+ error/warning totals\r\n\r\nBasically a plugin like this:\r\n```javascript\r\nusePlugin('pretty-solc');\r\n```\r\n```\r\nnpx buidler compile --pretty\r\n```\r\n\r\nIf there's any appetite here for a PR to decouple the output component, please just lmk and I will send one. \r\n ",
