    "body": "Hey @cgewecke!\r\n\r\nI really like this idea :) The compile task and its internal tasks are one of the oldest parts of Buidler. They were created when we were still in a prototyping phase. They need to be redesigned soon, before many plugins are created.\r\n\r\nApart from your idea, we have been discussing IRL that they should be redesign with multiple languages in mind. Do you have any other thought around this? Anything else you'd like to be able to do/modify in the compilation process?\r\n\r\nWe developed an experimental Vyper plugin, and we [ended up overriding the entire `compile` task](https://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/master/packages/buidler-vyper/src/index.ts#L13-L21), which is far from ideal.",
